    "slot_count": 5,
    "source_text": "儘管為遏制2019冠狀病毒病傳播的措施導致新業務價值減少至27.65億美元，但隨著外出限制放寬，銷售動力轉\n趨正面，並在2021年展開非常強勁的勢頭，首兩個月的新業務價值按年增長15%。我們規模龐大和持續增長的有\n效保單組合所帶來的高質素和經常性收入來源，帶動2020年稅後營運溢利增加5%，期內產生的基本自由盈餘則\n增長7%。截至2020年12月31日，內涵價值權益創新高，達672億美元，集團當地資本總和法覆蓋率為374%，足\n證我們雄厚的資本實力和嚴謹的財務管理。",
    "current_translation": "Although measures to contain the spread of COVID-19 resulted in New Business Value declining to US$2.765 billion, sales momentum turned positive as mobility restrictions eased, and we entered 2021 with very strong momentum, with New Business Value in the first two months growing 15% year-on-year. Our large and growing portfolio of in-force policies, which generates high-quality and recurring income streams, drove a 5% increase in Operating Profit After Tax in 2020, while Free Surplus generated during the period grew 7%. As at 31 December 2020, Embedded Value equity reached a record high of US$67.2 billion, and the Group's local capital aggregation method coverage ratio stood at 374%, demonstrating our strong capital position and prudent financial management."
